               </msContents>
               <physDesc>
                  <p>It seems reasonable to understand the word <foreign xml:lang="tam-Latn"
                        >eḻut°</foreign> in <foreign xml:lang="tam-Latn" facs="#d1">eḻut°
                        piṟiti</foreign> as an abbreviation for eḻutappaṭṭa (“that was copied”). (2)
                     The manuscript is described in detail by Emmanuel Francis in an online blog
                     post (https://tst.hypotheses.org/232). Francis points out that this colophon is
                     at the end of the main text of the <foreign xml:lang="tam-Latn"
                        >Caṅkaṟpanirākaraṇam</foreign>, although it was copied after its commentary,
                     which occupies a later portion of the manuscript with a different
                     foliation.</p>
               </physDesc>
            </msDesc>
